items.title: Trump wants voting changes. GOP majorities in Congress will try to make that happen
items.author: Associated Press
items.content:
Republicans in Congress plan to move quickly in 2025 in their effort to overhaul the nation’s voting procedures. They want to push through long-sought changes such as voter ID and proof-of-citizenship requirements. Read more: https://bit.ly/4gBmJgV

items.title: LIVE: Outside The Carter Center after Jimmy Carter dies at 100
items.author: Associated Press
items.content:
AP is live from outside The Carter Center in Atlanta after the 39th U.S. President Jimmy Carter died on Sunday, more than a year after entering hospice care, at his home in the small town of Plains, Georgia, where he and his wife, Rosalynn, who died at 96 in November 2023, spent most of their lives, The Carter Center said.

#jimmycarter #live #news

items.title: U.N. aid agencies bring supplies to Indonesian hospital in Gaza Strip
items.author: Associated Press
items.content:
Agencies delivered supplies to the Indonesia hospital in northern Gaza, as well as continuing an evacuation operation to get patients to Gaza City. The medical facility just outside of the territory’s largest refugee camp in Jabaliya has been under Israeli bombardment for weeks.

items.title: UN Secretary-General Guterres calls for peace and stability in New Year message
items.author: Associated Press
items.content:
In his New Year's recorded message, Antonio Guterres pledged to “forge a more peaceful, equal, stable and healthy future for all people" in 2025. He listed conflict but also climate change as the drivers of suffering with 10 of the hottest years on earth happening in the last 10 years, 2024 included. "Together, we can make 2025 a new beginning. Not as a world divided. But as nations united,” the Secretary-General said.

items.title: Gaza's women wrestle with a life stripped of privacy in crowded tent camps
items.author: Associated Press
items.content:
For Gaza’s women, the hardships of life in the territory’s sprawling tent camps are compounded by the daily humiliation of never having privacy. Women struggle to dress modestly while crowded into a tent with extended family members, including men, and with strangers only steps away in neighbouring tents. Access to menstrual products is limited too and makeshift toilets must be shared with dozens of other people. (AP video by Abed Al-Kareem Hana and Wafaa Shurafa) Read more here: https://bit.ly/4gSqCO9
